<p>The inference system seamlessly integrates with models produced by the t=
raining pipelines:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Classification Models</strong>: After merging LoRA weights (see=
 <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/4.1-classification-mo=
del-training" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underl=
ine">Classification Model Training</a>), the final model can be directly lo=
aded using its path</li>
<li><strong>Detection Models</strong>: Detection checkpoints from training =
(see <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/4.2-detection-mod=
el-training" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underli=
ne">Detection Model Training</a>) can be used immediately without additiona=
l processing</li>
</ul>
<p>Both model types are compatible with the same inference interface, with =
automatic detection of capabilities based on the <code class=3D"rounded-sm =
bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] b=
efore:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">with_detr</code> configurat=
ion flag.</p>
